  <span id="freeText10360537346051499109" style="display:none">Really should be a part of everyone's basic cooking library. Alice Waters gives plenty of ideas for modifying recipes to what is local and fresh for wherever you are. This makes me feel less like a food-loser when I can't find something for a recipe. Everything still turns out delightful.<br /><br />Sheela - Brussels Sprouts Gratin: Beautiful, special, tasty, crispy, cheesy awesome. Really. Lick the pan good. <br /><br />Me - Pot Roast: Succulent, perfect instructions. Made me feel like almost as good a cook as my momis.<br /><br />Molly - Red Pepper Soup: Molly knows her way around soup. This one was a perfect starter/side. So so satisfying.<br /><br />Gretchen - 1-2-3-4 Cake: I think I cut myself off after three pieces. Normally not a big cake eater (sheela's baking is the exception). I found this one really pleasant.<br /><br />I've also done her roast chicken for my husband and me. Idiot-proof and really special-tasting for a simple Sunday standard.</span>
