<div id="review_86941780" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/86941780" />
    <a title="Mary" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/576391-mary"><img alt="Mary" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1200036230p2/576391.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/86941780?book_show_action=true">Jan 26, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mary" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mary" href="/user/show/576391-mary">Mary</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/576391-mary?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/576391-mary?shelf=cookbook">cookbook</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer86941780" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17832936452431629728">I&apos;m sure it&apos;s a great book and all, but I lost interest immediately after the first few pages because of the misnomer. At first it talks about local and sustainable eating practices which is all fine and good...but then the following names of the recipes and the ingredients/methods required were ANYTHING but Simple. The word I would use is &quot;fancy.&quot; But, everyone else who reviewed said the recipes are TOO simple. Are we talking about the same book? Maybe I happened across a few recipes with ingre</span>
  <span id="freeText17832936452431629728" style="display:none">I'm sure it's a great book and all, but I lost interest immediately after the first few pages because of the misnomer. At first it talks about local and sustainable eating practices which is all fine and good...but then the following names of the recipes and the ingredients/methods required were ANYTHING but Simple. The word I would use is "fancy." But, everyone else who reviewed said the recipes are TOO simple. Are we talking about the same book? Maybe I happened across a few recipes with ingredients I've never heard of? I guess that's what I get for reading a few pages in the front, randomly picking a few in the middle, and then closing the book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17832936452431629728" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


